       <div class="crop">
        <a href="/opinion/opinion/2016327/small-traders-can-pull-their-weight"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2020/11/09/3803755.jpg" alt="Small traders can pull their weight" title="Small traders can pull their weight" srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2020/11/09/3803755_197.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2020/11/09/3803755_355.jpg 700w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/dcx/2020/11/09/3803755_371.jpg 350w"></a>
       </div> 
       <div class="list-detail"> 
        <h3> <a href="/opinion/opinion/2016327/small-traders-can-pull-their-weight">Small traders can pull their weight</a> </h3> 
        <p>When the Prayut Chan-o-cha government announced the launch of a populist 50-50 co-payment scheme as part of an economic stimulus package, some people questioned its virtue. I was among them. </p> 
        <div class="f-icon"> <span>04:30</span> <span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2016327/small-traders-can-pull-their-weight?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 3</a></span> 
        </div> 
        <div class="box-reporter"> <span class="img-profile"> <a href="/opinion/columnist/811"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115.jpg" title="Small traders can pull their weight" alt="Small traders can pull their weight" srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115_50.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115_50.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1565759115_50.jpg 700w"></a> </span> <span class="name"><a href="/opinion/columnist/811" class="link-unterline">Paritta Wangkiat</a></span> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
     <div class="col-list"> 
      <div class="list-v"> 
       <div class="list-detail"> 
        <h3> <a href="/opinion/opinion/2016463/it-never-rains-but-instead-it-pours">It never rains, but instead it pours</a> </h3> 
        <p>As the rainy season comes to an end, the population of Bangkok and its neighbouring provinces are readying to brave the return of PM2.5 dust particles that have been clouding the sky as reported recently by the Department of Pollution Control. A new working team has been set up to alert people of the situation and apparently, it will function just like the Centre for Covid-19 Situation Administration (CCSA). </p> 
        <div class="f-icon"> <span>04:30</span> <span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2016463/it-never-rains-but-instead-it-pours?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 12</a></span> 
        </div> 
        <div class="box-reporter"> <span class="img-profile"> <a href="/opinion/columnist/125"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1444302811.jpg" title="It never rains, but instead it pours" alt="It never rains, but instead it pours" srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1444302811_50.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1444302811_50.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/1444302811_50.jpg 700w"></a> </span> <span class="name"><a href="/opinion/columnist/125" class="link-unterline">Arusa Pisuthipan</a></span> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
     <div class="col-list"> 
      <div class="list-v"> 
       <div class="crop">
        <a href="/opinion/opinion/2016423/smarter-trade-deals-needed"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201109/c1_2016423_201109062429.jpg" alt="Smarter trade deals needed" title="Smarter trade deals needed" srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201109/c1_2016423_201109062429_197.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201109/c1_2016423_201109062429_355.jpg 700w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201109/c1_2016423_201109062429_371.jpg 350w"></a>
       </div> 
       <div class="list-detail"> 
        <h3> <a href="/opinion/opinion/2016423/smarter-trade-deals-needed">Smarter trade deals needed</a> </h3> 
        <p>Many Thais rejoiced after Joe Biden won the US presidential election over the weekend. But certain concerns remain as the US changes its leader; in particular, challenges currently facing Thailand's international trade. </p> 
        <div class="f-icon"> <span>04:30</span> <span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2016423/smarter-trade-deals-needed?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 4</a></span> 
        </div> 
        <div class="box-reporter"> <span class="img-profile"> <a href="/opinion/columnist/936"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/936.jpg" title="Smarter trade deals needed" alt="Smarter trade deals needed" srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/936_50.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/936_50.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/936_50.jpg 700w"></a> </span> <span class="name"><a href="/opinion/columnist/936" class="link-unterline">Editorial</a></span> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
