             </div> 
            </div> <!--div class="h-line"><a href=""></a></div--> 
            <h3><a href="/opinion/opinion/2015711/aung-san-suu-kyi-on-the-crest-of-a-red-wave-poised-to-be-swept-back-into-office">Aung San Suu Kyi: on the crest of a ‘red wave’ - poised to be swept back into office</a> </h3> 
            <p>The ruling National League for Democracy is expected to be returned, though likely with a reduced majority.</p> 
            <div class="f-icon"> <span class="fa-date-showmobi">7 Nov 2020 </span> <!-- show mobile --> <span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2015711/aung-san-suu-kyi-on-the-crest-of-a-red-wave-poised-to-be-swept-back-into-office?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 12</a></span> 
            </div> 
           </div> 
           <div class="listnews-img">
            <a href="/opinion/opinion/2015711/aung-san-suu-kyi-on-the-crest-of-a-red-wave-poised-to-be-swept-back-into-office"><img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/newdesign/assets/images/bg/default-pic-w600.jpg" class="img-fluid lazy" data-src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201107/c1_2015711_201107103230.jpg" title="Aung San Suu Kyi: on the crest of a ‘red wave’ - poised to be swept back into office" alt="Aung San Suu Kyi: on the crest of a ‘red wave’ - poised to be swept back into office" data-srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201107/c1_2015711_201107103230_126.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201107/c1_2015711_201107103230_216.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/content/20201107/c1_2015711_201107103230_216.jpg 700w"></a>
           </div> 
