            <div class="listnews-opinion"> 
             <div class="columnnist-img">
              <img src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/newdesign/assets/images/bg/default-pic-w600.jpg" class="lazy" data-src="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/26931485485935.jpg" alt="Post-Covid era ripe for renewed climate action" title="Post-Covid era ripe for renewed climate action" data-srcset="https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/26931485485935_32.jpg 350w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/26931485485935_32.jpg 500w,https://static.bangkokpost.com/media/columnist/26931485485935_32.jpg 700w">
             </div> 
             <div class="columnnist-name">
              BY <a href="/opinion/columnist/2693" class="link-unterline">Alok Sharma</a>
             </div> 
            </div> <!--div class="h-line"><a href=""></a></div--> 
            <h3><a href="/opinion/opinion/2015475/post-covid-era-ripe-for-renewed-climate-action">Post-Covid era ripe for renewed climate action</a> </h3> 
            <p>Last week we marked one year to go until the COP26 international climate summit, which will be hosted in the UK. This will be a pivotal moment for the world to come together and agree ambitious steps to prevent the catastrophic warming of our planet.</p> 
            <div class="f-icon"> <span class="fa-date-showmobi">7 Nov 2020 </span> <!-- show mobile --> <span class="ic-comment"><a href="/opinion/opinion/2015475/post-covid-era-ripe-for-renewed-climate-action?view_comment=1"><i class="icon-comment"></i> 1</a></span> 
            </div> 
           </div> 
